<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>In a 1994 case, the state Supreme Court held that viability is not a concern in fetal murder cases, and that prosecutors can pursue such a case &quot;as long as the state can show that the fetus has progressed beyond the embryonic stage of seven to eight weeks.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
